topic.title: Rational product names and common strings
topic.shortdesc: This file lists product names and common strings that are used in Rational content. If you must use a product name in your content, use the conref attribute of the keyword element to insert the names from this file into a DITA topic. If you use this technique, you can easily maintain topics if a product name changes by replacing this file instead of editing each file that contains the product name.

body.p: For the Rational guidelines on using product names in content, see

u.b: TO UPDATE OR EDIT THIS FILE, CONTACT THE REPRESENTATIVE FOR THE PRODUCTS THAT YOU WORK ON:

ul.li: For Rational products that are developed by Persistent Systems, contact Amy Laird.
For Rational products that are developed by IBM, contact your build representative to update your team version of this file.

body.p:
Before you ask to update the file, prepare this information:
The variations of the product name that you want to add (full, family, short)
Verification from the product editor, branding, and legal that the product name and their variations are approved
body.note: The IDWB trademark tool was run on this file so that the product names are properly trademarked in topics.

section.title: Wording for sample and tutorial prerequisites
section.p: This sample might require some optionally installable components. If you encounter errors or cannot find user interface options when you run the sample, ensure that you installed the appropriate optional components.
This tutorial might require some optionally installable components. To ensure that you installed the appropriate optional components, see the System requirements list.

p.note: After downloading the sample, import the sample project into your Eclipse workspace. To import the sample, click File ImportExisting projects into workspace Select archive file and select the downloaded sample project file.

section.title: Wording about server requirements for RAD and RAD CE samples and tutorials
section.p: To use this sample, you must have an application server installed and configured. To verify that a server runtime environment is available, click Window Preferences, expand Server, and then click Runtime Environments. You can use this pane to add, remove, or edit installed server runtime definitions. You can also download and install support for a new server.

To use this tutorial, you must have an application server installed and configured. To verify that a server runtime environment is available, click Window Preferences, expand Server, and then click Runtime Environments. You can use this pane to add, remove, or edit installed server runtime definitions. You can also download and install support for a new server.
